Because Cloudflare does not provide an official Pacman package, the best way to install it on CachyOS is to pull the pre-compiled binary directly from the Arch User Repository (AUR).

Here is the complete step-by-step process to get it installed, running, and connected.
Step 1: Install the Package

Open your terminal and use your AUR helper (paru or yay) to download and install the WARP client.
Bash

paru -S cloudflare-warp-bin

(Press Y to confirm the installation when prompted).
Step 2: Enable the Background Service

WARP relies on a system daemon to manage your network interfaces and route your traffic. If you skip this step, the client will immediately crash or throw an error when you try to connect.

Run this command to start the service and ensure it runs automatically every time you boot your computer:
Bash

sudo systemctl enable --now warp-svc.service

Step 3: Register and Connect

On Linux, Cloudflare WARP is managed entirely through the command line using the warp-cli tool.

    Register your device: This generates a free account/key on Cloudflare's servers for your machine.
    Bash

    warp-cli registration new

    (Note: You must accept their Terms of Service when prompted).

    Connect to the network:
    Bash

    warp-cli connect

Step 4: Verify Your Connection

To confirm that your web traffic is actually being routed and encrypted through Cloudflare's network, run this quick trace command:
Bash

curl https://www.cloudflare.com/cdn-cgi/trace/

Look at the output printed in your terminal. If you see warp=on near the bottom of the text block, your installation was successful and you are ready to browse!
